<TITLE> AL moving on council, reform </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 28(bdnews24.com)Awami League is moving to hold a council and reform its party constitution by a July 25 deadline, in line with electoral law. Party leaders have formed a panel for reform of the constitution and decided to hold tri-annual councils, said AL joint secretary Obaidul Qader. He was speaking after a four- hour meeting of the executive committee, with party chief Sheikh Hasina in the chair. "We will reform our constitution in line with the Representation of the People Order. A sub-committee has been constituted headed by the party president," said Quader. Sheikh Hasina urged party leaders to work together to realise the dream of a 'Digital Bangladesh', he said. "She also warned that a vested quarter staged the Peelkhana massacre to destabilise the popular government," said the joint secretary. Apart from organisational decisions, the committee also finalised programmes for observing Mujib Nagar Day and Bangla New Year in April. bd
